24/09/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Hungarian counterpart, Peter Medgyessy, signed an agreement Tuesday (23 September) concerning the law on the status of the ethnic Hungarian minorities in neighbouring countries.
The agreement envisions reciprocal standards for Romanians residing in Hungary.
In other news, Romania's Arges County has been selected to host a military exercise next month that is described as the most extensive of its kind ever to be held in Central or Eastern Europe.
(ACT Media - 24/09/03;
Rompres - 23/09/03)
